|bombs=<br>
** 84× [[Mark 82 bomb|Mk-82]] Air inflatable retarder (AIR) general purpose (GP) bombs<ref>As per B-1B Weapons Loading Checklist T.O. 1B-1B-33-2-1CL-8</ref>
** 81× Mk-82 low drag general purpose (LDGP) bombs<ref>As per B-1B Weapons Loading Checklist T.O. 1B-1B-33-2-1CL-7 (changed from 84 to 81 due to fit issues on 28X CBM with new tailkits)</ref>
** 84× [[Mark 82 bomb|Mk-62 ''Quickstrike'']] sea mines<ref>[http://www.airforce-magazine.com/MagazineArchive/Magazine%20Documents/Forms/DispForm.aspx?ID=408 "Bad to the B-ONE."] ''Air Force Magazine'', March 2007, p. 63. Retrieved: 25 July 2010.</ref>
** 24× [[Mark 84 bomb|Mk-84]] general purpose bombs
** 24× Mk-65 naval mines<ref name=Jenkins_p142/>
** 30× CBU-87/[[CBU-89 Gator|89]]/CBU-97 Cluster Bomb Units (CBU){{#tag:ref|As per B-1B Weapons Loading Checklist T.O. 1B-1B-33-2-1CL-13|group=N}}
** 30× CBU-103/104/105 [[Wind Corrected Munitions Dispenser]] (WCMD) CBUs
** 24× GBU-31 [[Joint Direct Attack Munition|JDAM]] GPS guided bombs (Mk-84 GP or BLU-109 warhead){{#tag:ref|both Mk-84 general purpose and [[BLU-109]] penetrating bombs|group=N}}
** 15× GBU-38 JDAM GPS guided bombs (Mk-82 GP warhead){{#tag:ref|As per B-1B Weapons Loading Checklist T.O. 1B-1B-33-2-1CL-12 Section 3.4 (Only six each in forward and intermediate bays and three each in the aft bay)|group=N}}
** 48x GBU-38 JDAM (using rotary launcher mounted multiple ejector racks)<ref name="Rivezzo">Rivezzo, Charles V. [http://www.eglin.af.mil/news/story.asp?id=123250570 "337 TES demonstrates ability to triple B-1 payload."] ''7th Bomb Wing Public Affairs, USAF'', 7 April 2011. Retrieved: 29 February 2012.</ref>
** 48x GBU-54 LaserJDAM (using rotary launcher mounted multiple ejector racks)<ref name="Rivezzo"/>
** 12× [[AGM-154 Joint Standoff Weapon]] (JSOW)
** 96× or 144× [[GBU-39 Small Diameter Bomb]] GPS guided bombs{{#tag:ref|96 if using four-packs, 144 if using six-packs. This capability has not yet been fielded on the B-1|group=N}} (not fielded on B-1 yet)
** 24× [[AGM-158 JASSM|AGM-158 Joint Air to Surface Standoff Missile]] (JASSM)
** 24× [[B61 nuclear bomb|B61]] or [[B83 nuclear bomb|B83]] nuclear bombs (no longer carried)<ref name=Jenkins_p142>{{harvnb|Jenkins|1999|p=142.}}</ref>

